wiki.text:
'Bifurcation' means the splitting of a main body into two parts.

'Bifurcation' or 'Bifurcated' may refer to:

*Bifurcation (law), the division of issues in a trial *Bifurcation theory, the
study of bifurcation in dynamical systems *River bifurcation, the forking of a
river into its distributaries *Bifurcation lake, a lake that flows into two
different drainage basins *Bifurcation of an incompressible flow, modeled by
squeeze mapping the fluid flow *Bifurcated bonding, in which a single hydrogen
atom participates in two hydrogen bonds *Aortic bifurcation, the point at which
the abdominal aorta bifurcates into the left and right common iliac arteries
